description: From quicken +‎ -s (suffix forming pluralia tantum, plurals of nouns, and the third-person singular indicative present tense of verbs).

entries.meaning: (chiefly Midlands (northern), Northern England, Northern Ireland, Scotland) Synonym of couch grass (“a species of grass, Elymus repens”); also, the underground rhizomes of this, and sometimes other grasses.
examples: Quickens are not confined to one species of grass.

entries.meaning: (chiefly Midlands (northern), Northern England, Northern Ireland, Scotland) plural of quicken
third-person singular simple present indicative form of quicken
